{"content":"---\ntitle: \"XSLT Extension Objects | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: dotnet-standard\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"VB\"\n  - \"CSharp\"\n  - \"C++\"\n  - \"jsharp\"\nms.assetid: a4ebdbad-087c-4cfe-acc0-17c48142f81a\ncaps.latest.revision: 3\nauthor: \"mairaw\"\nms.author: \"mairaw\"\nmanager: \"wpickett\"\n---\n# XSLT Extension Objects\nExtension objects are used to extend the functionality of style sheets. Extension objects are maintained by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> class.  \n  \n The following are advantages to using an extension object rather than embedded script:  \n  \n-   Provides better encapsulation and reuse of classes.  \n  \n-   Allows style sheets to be smaller and more maintainable.  \n  \n XSLT extension objects are added to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object using the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method. A qualified name and namespace URI are associated with the extension object at that time.  \n  \n> [!NOTE]\n>  The FullTrust permission set is required to call the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method. For more information, see [Code Access Security](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/23a20143-241d-4fe5-9d9f-3933fd594c03) and [NIB: Named Permission Sets](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/08250d67-c99d-4ab0-8d2b-b0e12019f6e3).  \n  \n The data types returned from extension objects are one of the four basic XPath data types of `number`, `string`, `Boolean`, and `node set`.  \n  \n Any method that is defined with the `params` keyword, which allows an unspecified number of parameters to be passed, is not currently supported by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XslCompiledTransform> class. XSLT style sheets that utilize any method defined with the `params` keyword will not work correctly. For details, see [params](~/docs/csharp/language-reference/keywords/params.md).  \n  \n### To use an XSLT extension object  \n  \n1.  Create an <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object and add the extension object using <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method.  \n  \n2.  Call the extension object from the style sheet.  \n  \n3.  Pass the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XslCompiledTransform.Transform%2A> method.  \n  \n## See Also  \n [XSLT Transformations](../../../../docs/standard/data/xml/xslt-transformations.md)   \n [XSLT Security Considerations](../../../../docs/standard/data/xml/xslt-security-considerations.md)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,51],"content":"XSLT Extension Objects | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"XSLT Extension Objects | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,39]}]},{"pos":[396,418],"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","linkify":"XSLT Extension Objects","nodes":[{"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","pos":[0,22]}]},{"content":"Extension objects are used to extend the functionality of style sheets.","pos":[419,490]},{"content":"Extension objects are maintained by the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList&gt;</ph> class.","pos":[491,576],"source":" Extension objects are maintained by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> class."},{"content":"The following are advantages to using an extension object rather than embedded script:","pos":[583,669]},{"content":"Provides better encapsulation and reuse of classes.","pos":[679,730]},{"content":"Allows style sheets to be smaller and more maintainable.","pos":[740,796]},{"content":"XSLT extension objects are added to the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList&gt;</ph> object using the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[803,967],"source":"XSLT extension objects are added to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object using the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltAr